comments.undefined: Master in Computational Biology Protein Ontology (MCBPO), is an ontology whose purpose is to provide a consensual knowledge model of proteins.

comment.undefined: Class that implies the numeric length of a protein.  It references the class Value of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Class for the protein instances. It references the class Protein of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Class that implies which organism has a protein. It references the class Species of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Proteins that catalyze metabolic reactions (enzymes).
Proteins that provide a structural framework for cells and organs.
Class that implies which gene encodes a protein. It references the class Gene of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Class that implies what process a protein is involved in. It references the class Biological Process of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Class that implies where in the cell a certain protein is located. It references the class Subcellular Structure of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
Class that implies a unit for the length of the protein. It references the class Subcellular Structure of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition, and in our case always takes the value amino acids.
Proteins that sere as biological reserves for metal ions and amino acids.
Proteins that transport molecules and metabolites inside or accross the cell.
Proteins thaat provide immunity (immunological) or cause an immune response (infectious).
Proteins involved in the communication between cells.
Proteins that regulate the genetic expression.
Class that implies the function of a protein. It references the class Protein Function of the ontology NCI Thesaurus OBO Edition.
